    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "e86512ba_68012f98",
        "filename": "src/chromiumos/tast/bundle/args.go",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 294,
      "author": {
        "id": 1118346
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-10-09T09:58:42Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I want to avoid adding new command line flags to bundles because it is not scable to further extension. New protocol should be added as gRPC services or using protocol buffers.\n\nIn this case runtime variable data is needed before starting gRPC server (tricky!), so it is likely we have to deal with raw protocol buffers.\n\nCan you define a new protocol buffer message, named like BundleRPCServerParams, and send it over the raw SSH channel from the client before starting gRPC server? Please note that protocol buffer messages are not delimited, so we need to send the message length first.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 285,
        "startChar": 2,
        "endLine": 294,
        "endChar": 101
      },
      "revId": "053fede55501f5eb6a3c5e6a21e1c2e93bdcaf6c",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "ecbf3031_1f6edc22",
        "filename": "src/chromiumos/tast/bundle/args.go",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 294,
      "author": {
        "id": 1400377
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-10-16T19:50:30Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "As described in the commit message, a new Management Service is designed to set management data (testvars only at this time) before other service starts to call. Please check if this works for you.",
      "parentUuid": "e86512ba_68012f98",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 285,
        "startChar": 2,
        "endLine": 294,
        "endChar": 101
      },
      "revId": "053fede55501f5eb6a3c5e6a21e1c2e93bdcaf6c",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "1c040ae6_ef3f0f11",
        "filename": "src/chromiumos/tast/bundle/args.go",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 294,
      "author": {
        "id": 1118346
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-10-19T06:03:06Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Thanks for adding protocol buffer definitions!\n\nHowever, setting runtime variables after starting a gRPC server results in introducing a mutability to testing.ServiceState; that is, when testing.ServiceState is constructed at the first time, it doesn\u0027t contain runtime variables data, but it will get some point later. I really want to avoid this because it may cause subtle bugs later (e.g. data races).\n\nSo, as I mentioned in the previous comment, could you try passing runtime variables data *before* starting a gRPC server?",
      "parentUuid": "ecbf3031_1f6edc22",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 285,
        "startChar": 2,
        "endLine": 294,
        "endChar": 101
      },
      "revId": "053fede55501f5eb6a3c5e6a21e1c2e93bdcaf6c",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "9d301636_6dda7fba",
        "filename": "src/chromiumos/tast/bundle/args.go",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 294,
      "author": {
        "id": 1400377
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-10-19T19:56:01Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Hi Shuhei,\n\nNo problem for using raw protocol buffer. Before I change, I want to discuss the two possible approaches:\n\n1 Add a command line flag -bundlerpcserverparams to bundle runner, but the value of the flag is encoded as protocol buffer data and can be further extended in the future.\n2 Start the the bundle process with RPCMode, then wait for BundleRPCServerParams messages (encoded with protocol buffer) in the bundle process before it starts gRPC services. With this approach, the bundle process will be in an intermediate state waiting for messages from SSH streaming IO. Handling of IO timeout and message error need to be considered as well.\n\nDo you prefer the first or second approach?\n\nThanks,\nXibin",
      "parentUuid": "1c040ae6_ef3f0f11",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 285,
        "startChar": 2,
        "endLine": 294,
        "endChar": 101
      },
      "revId": "053fede55501f5eb6a3c5e6a21e1c2e93bdcaf6c",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba"
    },
    {
