      "message": "That\u0027s a very good point that panics in gRPC services result in process crash! Thanks for letting me know.\n\nI think it\u0027s a general problem in gRPC services rather than being specific to testing.ServiceState.Var. I filed crbug.com/1139778 to track this.\n\nAssuming we\u0027ll resolve the issue later, I think we can align the behavior between testing.State.Var and testing.ServiceState.Var. So can you just panic when a var is not declared?",
